{"title_page": "2012 Metro Manila Film Festival", "text_new": "{{Infobox film festival\n| name           = 2012 Metro Manila Film Festival<br/>{{small|38th Metro Manila Film Festival}}\n| logo           = 38th Metro Manila Film Festival Logo.jpg\n| logo_alt       = \n| logo_size      = \n| image          = \n| image_alt      = \n| image_size     = \n| caption        = \n| awards         = [[2012 Metro Manila Film Festival#Awards|Gabi ng Parangal]] ({{literal translation|Awards Night}})\n| films          = \n| host           = \n| number         = 8\n| date           = {{Start date|2012|12|25}} to {{End date|2013|01|08}}\n| language       = \n| website        = \n| chronology     = MMFF\n| preceded_by    = [[2011 Metro Manila Film Festival|37th ed.]] \n| followed_by    = [[2013 Metro Manila Film Festival|39th ed.]]\n}}\nThe 38th '''[[Metro Manila Film Festival]]''' (MMFF) is a part of the annual film festival in [[Metro Manila, Philippines]] held from December 25, 2012 until January 8, 2013. During the festival, no foreign films are shown in Philippine theaters in order to showcase locally produced films (except in select [[3D film|3D]] cinemas and [[IMAX]] theaters).\n\n==Entries==\nIn the last week of May 2012, film producers and companies already submitted their scripts in participation with the festival. However, it will still be reviewed by the [[Metropolitan Manila Development Authority]] to sort out entries. Of the fifteen film entries submitted, eight were chosen as the official entries. ''[[Mga Kwento ni Lola Basyang]]'' was one of the eight entries chosen, but the producer sent a letter to MMDA to pull out of the film festival. On October 19, 2012 it was replaced by [[Nora Aunor]]'s ''[[Thy Womb]]''.<ref>[http://reynthology.blogspot.com/2012/10/thy-womb-replaces-lola-basyang-as.html 'Thy Womb' replaces 'Lola Basyang' as MMFF 2012 official entry] ''Reyn's Room''. Retrieved November 18, 2012.</ref>\n\nHere are the eight official entries:<ref>[http://www.mb.com.ph/articles/362358/2012-mmff-official-entries-bared 2012 MMFF Official Entries] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120927050350/http://www.mb.com.ph/articles/362358/2012-mmff-official-entries-bared |date=2012-09-27 }} ''Manila Bulletin''. Retrieved 06-17-2012.</ref>\n\n=== Official entries ===\nThe eight films with the highest lobbying placement fee paid were chosen to be the official entries.<ref name=\"PinouF\">[http://www.pinoypundit.net/2012/06/mmff-2012-list-of-entries-submitted-by.html 2012 MMFF Possible Entries] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120619055614/http://www.pinoypundit.net/2012/06/mmff-2012-list-of-entries-submitted-by.html |date=2012-06-19 }} ''Pinoy Pundit''. Retrieved June 14, 2012.</ref><ref name=\"MBmmff\">[https://archive.today/20130113184240/http://www.mb.com.ph/articles/361603/14-scripts-beat-mmff-deadline 14 Scripts beat MMFF deadline] ''Manila Bulletin Online''. Retrieved June 14, 2012</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size: 95%\"\n|-\n! width=\"20%\"|Title  !! width=\"50%\"| Starring !! width=\"15%\"| Studio !! width=\"15%\"|Director !! Genre !! width=\"2%\"|Reference\n|-\n| '''''[[Si Agimat, si Enteng Kabisote at si Ako]]''''' || [[Vic Sotto]], [[Bong Revilla Jr.]] and [[Judy Ann Santos]] || [[Octoarts Films]], <br/> M-Zet Productions, <br/> Imus Productions, <br/> [[APT Entertainment]], and <br/> [[GMA Films]] || Tony Reyes || [[Fantasy]]/[[Comedy]]/[[Action film|Action]] ||<ref>[http://pep.ph/news/34467/vic-sotto-on-rumored-cool-off-with-pauleen-luna-natatawa-na-lang-ako-ang-importante-alam-nrsquoyo-naman-kung-ano-ang-tunay-na-nangyayarirdquo Vic Sotto- Bong Revilla- Judy Ann Santos movie] ''Philippine Entertainment Portal''. Retrieved June 14, 2012</ref>\n|- \n| '''''[[El Presidente (film)|El Presidente]]''''' || [[E.R. Ejercito]], [[Cristine Reyes]] || Scenema Concept International, <br/> CMB Films, and <br/> [[VIVA Films]] || Mark Meilly || [[Action film|Action]]/[[Historical drama]]/ [[Thriller (genre)|Thriller]]  ||<ref>[http://www.abs-cbnnews.com/entertainment/08/09/11/nora-aunor-starts-filming-el-presidente Nora Aunor starts filming El presidente] ''ABS-CBN News''. Retrieved June 14, 2012</ref><ref>[http://www.mb.com.ph/articles/306806/er-ejercito-el-presidente EL Presidente starts filming] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110302060338/http://www.mb.com.ph/articles/306806/er-ejercito-el-presidente |date=2011-03-02 }} ''Manila Bulletin''. Retrieved June 14, 2012</ref>\n|-\n| '''''[[One More Try (film)|One More Try]]''''' || [[Angel Locsin]], [[Dingdong Dantes]], [[Angelica Panganiban]], and [[Zanjoe Marudo]] || [[Star Cinema]] || Ruel S. Bayani  || [[Drama film|Drama]] ||<ref>[http://www.push.com.ph/features/7849/dingdong-dantes-says-he-will-play-his-most-daring-role-in-one-more-try/ Dingdong Dantes plays most daring role in One More Try] ''PUSH''. Retrieved June 1, 2012</ref><ref>[http://www.pep.ph/news/34065/dingdong-dantes-on-working-with-angel-locsin-i-hope-na-in-cases-like-this-hindi-magkaroon-ng-double-standardhellip One More Try Movie for MMFF 2012] ''Philippine Entertainment Portal''. Retrieved June 14, 2012</ref>\n|-\n| '''''[[Shake, Rattle and Roll Fourteen: The Invasion]]''''' || [[Vhong Navarro]], [[Lovi Poe]], [[Dennis Trillo]], [[Paulo Avelino]], [[Mart Escudero]], [[Janice de Belen]], [[Herbert Bautista]] || [[Regal Films]] || [[Chito S. Ro\u00f1o]] || [[Horror film|Horror Suspense]] ||<ref name=\"PinouF\" />\n|-\n| '''''[[Sisterakas]]''''' || [[Kris Aquino]], [[Ai-Ai de las Alas]], [[Vice Ganda]], [[Kathryn Bernardo]], [[Daniel Padilla]], and [[Xyriel Manabat]] || [[Star Cinema]] and <br/> [[Viva Films]] || [[Wenn V. Deramas]] || [[Comedy film|Comedy]] ||<ref>[http://viceganda.net/vice-ganda-and-kris-aquino-to-join-forces-in-mmff-2012/ Vice-Kris Movie] ''Vice Ganda Web''. Retrieved June 14, 2012.</ref><ref>[http://www.abs-cbnnews.com/entertainment/06/16/12/kris-vice-ganda-team-mmff-entry Kris-Vice Team up for MMFF this 2012] ''ABS-CBN Entertainment News''. Retrieved 06-17-2012</ref>\n|-\n| '''''[[Sosy Problems]]''''' || [[Heart Evangelista]], [[Rhian Ramos]], [[Solenn Heussaff]], [[Bianca King]], [[Benjamin Alves]], [[Mikael Daez]] and [[Aljur Abrenica]] || [[GMA Films]] || Andoy Ranay || [[Comedy]] ||<ref>[https://archive.today/20121208232520/http://www.philstar.com/Article.aspx?articleId=804340&publicationSubCategoryId=96 Cono Problems for MMFF] ''Philippine Star''. Retrieved June 14, 2012</ref><ref>[https://archive.today/20130208163043/http://www.philstar.com/Article.aspx?articleId=818050&publicationSubCategoryId=70 Conyo Problems \"in\" for MMFF 2012] ''The Philippine Star''. Retrieved 06-17-2012.</ref>\n|-\n| '''''[[The Strangers (2012 film)|The Strangers]]''''' || [[Julia Montes]], [[Enrique Gil]], [[JM De Guzman]] and [[Enchong Dee]] || Quantum Films, <br/> MJM Productions  || Lawrence Fajardo || [[Horror film|Horror]] ||<ref>[http://rodmagaru.com/tag/vii-quantum-films-horror-movie-the-strangers-julia-montes/ Julia Montes to do a horror movie] ''Rod Magaru Website''. Retrieved June 14, 2012</ref>\n|-\n| '''''[[Thy Womb]]''''' || [[Nora Aunor]], [[Bembol Roco]], [[Lovi Poe]], [[Mercedes Cabral]]  || Centerstage Productions  || Brillante Mendoza || [[Drama]] ||<ref name=\"MBmmff\" /><ref name=\"THY\">{{cite web|url=http://www.abs-cbnnews.com/lifestyle/10/19/12/thy-womb-gets-last-minute-slot-mmff|title='Thy Womb' gets last-minute slot in MMFF|publisher=[[ABS-CBN]] News|accessdate=October 19, 2012}}</ref>\n|-\n|}\n\n===New Wave entries===\nThe ''New Wave'' films were screened from December 18 to 22 as a prelude to the MMFF opening on December 25, 2012.<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.philstar.com/breaking-news/2012/12/11/884857/mmda-screens-student-films-part-mmff | title=MMDA screens student films as part of MMFF |author= Mike Frialde | newspaper=[[Philippine Star]]  | date=December 11, 2012 | accessdate=August 11, 2015}}</ref> This year, the MMFF will continue the tradition of supporting independent films through a bigger, better and bolder ''[[Metro Manila Film Festival New Wave Awards|New Wave]]'' Section.\n* ''Ad Ignorantiam'' - Armando Y. Lao\n* ''Gayak'' -  Ronaldo Bertubin\n* ''In Nomine Matris'' - Will Fredo\n* ''Paglaya sa Tanikala'' - Michael Angelo Dagn\u00f1alan\n* ''The Grave Bandits'' - Tyrone Acierto\n\n===Student shorts===\nThese films were screened along with the ''New Wave'' entries.\n* ''Kinse'' - Nikki Del Carmen, [[Mowelfund Film Institute]]\n* ''Lugaw'' - Nikko Arcega & Minette Palcon, [[Mowelfund Film Institute]]\n* ''Manibela'' - Bobby Pagotan, [[Far Eastern University]]\n* ''Obsesyon'' - Danny Yu, [[Mowelfund Film Institute]]\n* ''Pukpok'' - Joaquin Pantaleon, [[De La Salle University]]\n* ''Ritwal'' - Samantha Fe Solidum, [[University of San Carlos]]\n* ''Rolyo'' - Rea Abalos, [[Mowelfund Film Institute]]\n* ''Sonata'' - Moises Anthony Cruz, [[University of the Philippines Diliman]]\n* ''Tagad'' - Daniel Bautista, [[University of San Carlos]]\n* ''Tsansa'' - John Paul Pepito, [[Cebu Normal University]]\n\n== Awards ==\n{{Infobox film awards\n| name             = 2012 Metro Manila Film Festival<br/>Gabi ng Parangal\n| number           = 38\n| award            = [[Metro Manila Film Festival]]\n| award_link       = \n| image            = \n| date             = {{Start date|2012|12|27}}\n| site         =Meralco Theater, [[Pasig]]\n| best_picture = ''[[One More Try (film)|One More Try]]''\n| most_wins    = ''[[El Presidente (film)|El Presidente]]'' and ''[[Thy Womb]]'' (7)\n| most_nominations = \n| network          = [[5 (TV channel)|TV5]]\n| website          = \n| last         = [[37th Metro Manila Film Festival|37th]]\n| next         = [[39th Metro Manila Film Festival|39th]]\n}}\nThe 38th Metro Manila Film Festival Awards Night was held at the Meralco Theater in [[Ortigas Center]], [[Pasig City]] on December 27, 2012.<ref>{{cite web|title=MMFF 2012 Winners|url=http://noypistuff.blogspot.com/2012/12/38th-metro-manila-film-festival-mmff.html|accessdate=December 28, 2012}}</ref>\n\nWinners are listed first and highlighted in '''boldface.'''<ref>http://noypistuff.blogspot.com/2012/12/38th-metro-manila-film-festival-mmff.html</ref>\n\n===Major awards===\n[[File:Brillante Mendoza at the 69th Venice International Film Festival, September 2012.jpg|right|thumb|150px|[[Brillante Mendoza]], Best Director winner]]\n[[File:Dingdong Dantes at the Eat Bulaga! Press Conference, July 2008.JPG|right|thumb|150px|[[Dingdong Dantes]], Best Actor winner]]\n[[File:Nora Aunor at the 69th Venice International Film Festival, September 2012.jpg|right|thumb|150px|[[Nora Aunor]], Best Actress winner and Female Star of the Night]]\n[[File:Cesar Montano.jpg|right|thumb|150px|[[Cesar Montano]], Best Supporting Actor winner]]\n[[File:Apl de ap 061014 2.jpg|right|thumb|150px|[[Apl.de.ap]], Best Original Theme Song performer (with Jamir Garcia)]]\n[[File:JosephEstradajf1486.JPG|right|thumb|150px|[[Joseph Estrada]], Male Star of the Night]]\n{| class=wikitable style=\"width=\"150%\"\n|-\n! style=\"background:#EEDD82;\" ! style=\"width=\"50%\" | [[Metro Manila Film Festival Award for Best Picture|Best Picture]]\n! style=\"background:#EEDD82;\" ! style=\"width=\"50%\" | [[Metro Manila Film Festival Award for Best Director|Best Director]]\n|-\n| valign=\"top\" |\n* '''''[[One More Try (film)|One More Try]]'' - [[Star Cinema]]'''\n** ''[[El Presidente (film)|El Presidente]]'' - Scenema Concept International and [[Viva Films]] {{small|(2nd Best Picture)}}\n** ''[[Sisterakas]]'' - [[Star Cinema]] and [[Viva Films]] {{small|(3rd Best Picture)}}\n** ''[[The Strangers (2012 film)|The Strangers]]'' - Quantum Films and MJM Productions\n** ''[[Thy Womb]]'' - Centerstage Production\n| valign=\"top\" |\n* '''[[Brillante Mendoza]] - ''[[Thy Womb]]'''''\n** [[Ruel S. Bayani]] - ''[[One More Try (film)|One More Try]]''\n|-\n! style=\"background:#EEDD82;\" ! style=\"width=\"50%\" | [[Metro Manila Film Festival Award for Best Actor|Best Actor]]\n! style=\"background:#EEDD82;\" ! style=\"width=\"50%\" | [[Metro Manila Film Festival Award for Best Actress|Best Actress]]\n|-\n| valign=\"top\" |\n* '''[[Dingdong Dantes]] - ''[[One More Try (film)|One More Try]]'''''\n** [[E.R. Ejercito]] - ''[[El Presidente (film)|El Presidente]]''\n** [[Herbert Bautista]] - ''[[Shake, Rattle and Roll Fourteen: The Invasion]]''\n** [[Vice Ganda]] - ''[[Sisterakas]]''\n** [[Bembol Roco]] - ''[[Thy Womb]]''\n| valign=\"top\" |\n* '''[[Nora Aunor]] - ''[[Thy Womb]]'''''\n** [[Angelica Panganiban]] - ''[[One More Try (film)|One More Try]]''\n** [[Angel Locsin]] - ''[[One More Try (film)|One More Try]]''\n** [[Janice de Belen]] - ''[[Shake, Rattle and Roll Fourteen: The Invasion]]''\n** [[Judy Ann Santos]] - ''[[Si Agimat, si Enteng Kabisote at si Ako]]''\n|-\n! style=\"background:#EEDD82;\" ! style=\"width=\"50%\" | [[Metro Manila Film Festival Award for Best Supporting Actor|Best Supporting Actor]]\n! style=\"background:#EEDD82;\" ! style=\"width=\"50%\" | [[Metro Manila Film Festival Award for Best Supporting Actress|Best Supporting Actress]]\n|-\n| valign=\"top\" |\n* '''[[Cesar Montano]] - ''[[El Presidente (film)|El Presidente]]'''''\n** [[Zanjoe Marudo]] - ''[[One More Try (film)|One More Try]]''\n| valign=\"top\" |\n* '''Wilma Doesnt - ''[[Sisterakas]]'''''\n** [[Gina Pareno]] - ''[[One More Try (film)|One More Try]]'''''\n|-\n! style=\"background:#EEDD82;\" ! style=\"width=\"50%\" | [[Metro Manila Film Festival Award for Best Child Performer|Best Child Performer]]\n! style=\"background:#EEDD82;\" ! style=\"width=\"50%\" | [[Metro Manila Film Festival Award for Best Original Story|Best Original Story]]\n|-\n| valign=\"top\" |\n* '''Miguel Vergara - ''[[One More Try (film)|One More Try]]'''''\n| valign=\"top\" |\n* '''Henry Burgos - ''[[Thy Womb]]'''''\n|-\n! style=\"background:#EEDD82;\" ! style=\"width=\"50%\" | [[Metro Manila Film Festival Award for Best Screenplay|Best Screenplay]]\n! style=\"background:#