owcase locally produced films (except in select [[3D film|3D]] cinemas and [[IMAX]] theaters).\n\n==Entries==\nIn the last week of May 2012, film producers and companies already submitted their scripts in participation with the festival. However, it will still be reviewed by the [[Metropolitan Manila Development Authority]] to sort out entries. Of the fifteen film entries submitted, eight were chosen as the official entries. ''[[Mga Kwento ni Lola Basyang]]'' was one of the eight entries chosen, but the producer sent a letter to MMDA to pull out of the film festival. On October 19, 2012 it was replaced by [[Nora Aunor]]'s ''[[Thy Womb]]''.<ref>[http://reynthology.blogspot.com/2012/10/thy-womb-replaces-lola-basyang-as.html 'Thy Womb' replaces 'Lola Basyang' as MMFF 2012 official entry] ''Reyn's Room''. Retrieved November 18, 2012.</ref>\n\nHere are the eight official entries:<ref>[http://www.mb.com.ph/articles/362358/2012-mmff-official-entries-bared 2012 MMFF Official Entries] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120927050350/http://www.mb.com.ph/articles/362358/2012-mmff-official-entries-bared |date=2012-09-27 }} ''Manila Bulletin''. Retrieved 06-17-2012.</ref>\n\n=== Official entries ===\nThe eight films with the highest lobbying placement fee paid were chosen to be the official entries.<ref name=\"PinouF\">[http://www.pinoypundit.net/2012/06/mmff-2012-list-of-entries-submitted-by.html 2012 MMFF Possible Entries] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120619055614/http://www.pinoypundit.net/2012/06/mmff-2012-list-of-entries-submitted-by.html |date=2012-06-19 }} ''Pinoy Pundit''. Retrieved June 14, 2012.</ref><ref name=\"MBmmff\">[https://archive.today/20130113184240/http://www.mb.com.ph/articles/361603/14-scripts-beat-mmff-deadline 14 Scripts beat MMFF deadline] ''Manila Bulletin Online''. Retrieved June 14, 2012</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size: 95%\"\n|-\n! width=\"20%\"|Title  !! width=\"50%\"| Starring !! width=\"15%\"| Studio